stylometry: @RISK performs a risk analysis to show how many possible outcomes in your Excel Spreedsheet, and tells you how likely they are to occur. This means you can judge which risks to take and which to avoid, allowing for the best desicion making under certainty. It also gives you the Standard DEviation of each possibility so that you can pick how relaible your variable is that you want. 5 simulations means that you are running 5 seperate possible outcomes throuhgt the problem and seeing the results of each. This will give you a much closer and exact answer to choose from when deciding which variable to choose.
